Peru Stocks: Alicorp, Buenaventura, Minera IRL, Rio Alto

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-09-20T18:23:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/peru-stocks-alicorp-buenaventura-minera-irl-rio-alto.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:56 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index gained for the sixth session in
seven, rising 0.2 percent to 20,358.69. The MSCI All Peru Capped
Index climbed 0.8 percent to 2,655.43.  Industrial shares gained after U.S. stocks rebounded, said
Estefany Castillo, an analyst at Scotiabank Peru.  Alicorp SA (ALICORC1)  (ALICORC1 PE), Peru’s largest foodstuff maker,
rose 3.4 percent to 6 soles.  Cementos Lima SA (CEMLIMI1)  (CEMLIMC1 PE), the
country’s biggest cement maker, climbed 0.9 percent to 2.20
soles.  Cementos Pacasmayo SAA (CPACASI1)  (CPACASC1 PE), the Hochschild
Group’s cement producer, gained 0.8 percent to 5.20 soles.  Gold miners rose as futures advanced in New York.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, jumped 4 percent to $47.02 after
partner Gold Fields Ltd. announced an increase in resources at
their Chucapaca gold deposit.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K.
minerals explorer with a gold mine in Peru, rose 2.4 percent to
$1.26.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold
exploration company, rose 4.1 percent to $3.28.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  